    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>"Nazca" and "Nasca" are commonly used interchangeably, but generally prefer the use of Nazca to describe the region, town, and river; and Nasca to refer to the period and culture that inhabited this area.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>納斯卡的原文有兩種拼法：「Nazca」或「Nasca」；兩者可替換使用。但一般常用「Nazca」來描述地區、城鎮及河流，而「Nasca」則指存在於該地區的時期與文化。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Nazca" e "Nasca" são comumente usados ​​de forma intercambiável, mas geralmente preferem o uso de Nazca para descrever a região, cidade e rio; e Nasca para se referir ao período e cultura que habitou esta área.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
